# AGD_OPE.1 Operational user guidance
## Developer action elements

### AGD_OPE.1.1D
The developer shall provide operational user guidance.

implementation status: not implemented

the build :

- generates and runs the end-to-end tests based on the processes in the model TODO
- for a TOE with GUI the end-to-end tests create screenshots of all the process steps involving the GUI TODO
- generates a list of procedures for each roles, containing TODO
  - all the process steps involving the given role TODO
  - the process steps performed by the TOE in response to the steps performed by the role TODO
  - the objectives and behaviours associated with the process steps TODO
  - the screenshot of the UI at that step if exist TODO
  - the business objects with TODO
    - their value set
    - the security notes associated with them 
    - security labels where accociated

The metamodel constraints amke sure that:

If there are operational modes defined (beyond normal operation), then:

- the operational modes are the values of a system parameter
- the system parameter for operational modes is persisted and initialized on startup
- there are behaviours defined for each of the operational modes

The metamodel constraints ensure the above rules, and the build generates documentation which for each operational modes TODO
- lists the behaviours associated with them
- lists the process steps associated with the behaviours
- as with other behaviours, these behaviours are shown in the generated user documentation.


## Content and presentation elements

### AGD_OPE.1.1C
The operational user guidance shall describe, for each user role, the user-accessible
functions and privileges that should be controlled in a secure processing environment,
including appropriate warnings.

The procedure description for each role, especially the UI and the business objects

How to adapt:

- model according to the metamodel
- associate security notes to the business objects representing security parameters

What to check:

- security notes are associated and have appropriate content
- the generated procedure documentation

### AGD_OPE.1.2C
The operational user guidance shall describe, for each user role, how to use the available
interfaces provided by the TOE in a secure manner.

How to adapt:

- model according to the metamodel
- make sure that the behaviours associated with the process steps correctly describe the reasons and nuances of each step
- place security notes where appropriate

What to check:

- the description of UI and their usage in the generated procedure documentation

### AGD_OPE.1.3C
The operational user guidance shall describe, for each user role, the available functions
and interfaces, in particular all security parameters under the control of the user,
indicating secure values as appropriate.

The description of the business objects, the security notes and value sets achieve this.

How to adapt:

- model according to the metamodel
- include security labels as fields where they are needed
- place security notes to business objects and their value sets where needed


How to check:

- check that appropriate security notes with relevant content are associated to business objects and their value sets where needed
- check that needed security labels are part of the business entities


### AGD_OPE.1.4C
The operational user guidance shall, for each user role, clearly present each type of
security-relevant event relative to the user-accessible functions that need to be
performed, including changing the security characteristics of entities under the control of
the TSF.

The process initiating events and the steps performed by the TOE in response to the steps performed by the user cover this

How to adapt:

- model according to the metamodel
- associate security notes with events and process steps where appropriate

How to check:

- check that appropriate security notes with relevant content are associated to events and process steps

### AGD_OPE.1.5C
The operational user guidance shall identify all possible modes of operation of the TOE
(including operation following failure or operational error), their consequences and
implications for maintaining secure operation.

See AGD_OPE.1.1D for operational modes.

How to adapt:

- If there are multiple operational modes
  - Make sure that a parameter is marked as operational mode
  - Make sure that the parameter marked as perational mode is persisted upon change
  - Make sure that the parameter arked as operational mode is read upon startup
  - Make sure that metamodel constraints are satisfied
  - Make sure that behaviours associated with operational modes are clearly state the operation mode they are relevant to
  - Make sure that operational mode behaviours are associated with the appropriate process steps

How to check:

- Check whether operational modes are defined. If so:
 - make sure that the behaviours associated with operational modes are clear and conscise, and they refer to the relevant operational mode(s)
 - make sure that the behaviours associated with operational modes are associated to all relevant process steps

### AGD_OPE.1.6C
The operational user guidance shall, for each user role, describe the security controls to
be followed in order to fulfil the security objectives for the operational environment as
described in the ST.

The process initiating events and the steps performed by the TOE in response to the steps performed by the user cover this

How to adapt:

- model according to the metamodel
- associate security notes with events and process steps where appropriate

How to check:

- check that appropriate security notes with relevant content are associated to events and process steps


### AGD_OPE.1.7C
The operational user guidance shall be clear and reasonable.

How to adapt:

- Make sure that all metamodel constraints are satisfied
- Make sure that all behaviours are clearly and consisely documented and associated with the appropriate process steps

How to check:
- Test all user procedures following the user guidance, and make sure that the documentation is clear and reasonable.

## Evaluator action elements

### AGD_OPE.1.1E
The evaluator shall confirm that the information provided meets all requirements for
content and presentation of evidence.

See "how to check" sections above.

